---
import PublicLayout from '../layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="smagile's privacy policy. How we collect, use, and protect your personal data in accordance with GDPR."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-grey-900 dark:text-white">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-grey-700 dark:text-warm-200">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-8 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        smagile is a trading name of SM Agile Ltd, a company registered in England and Wales.
        We are the data controller for any personal data collected through this website.
      </p>

      <h2>What data we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect personal data only when you provide it to us voluntarily, for example:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name and email address when you contact us or book a consultation</li>
        <li>Any additional information you choose to share in your message</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use your data</h2>
      <p>We use your personal data solely for the purpose for which it was provided:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to your enquiry</li>
        <li>To arrange and deliver consultation calls or services you have requested</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use your data for marketing unless you have given explicit consent.
        We do not sell or share your data with third parties for their own purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>Lawful basis for processing</h2>
      <p>
        We process your personal data on the basis of legitimate interest (responding to your
        enquiry) or your explicit consent where required.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>This website uses cookies in two categories:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Essential cookies</strong> (always active): these are strictly necessary for the
          site to function, such as your theme preference and cookie consent choice.
          No personal data is collected.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics cookies</strong> (opt-in only): if you consent via the cookie banner,
          we use Google Analytics to understand how visitors use the site. This includes
          pages visited, time on site, and general location (country level). IP addresses
          are anonymised. You can withdraw consent at any time via the "Cookie Preferences"
          link in the footer.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We also use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is a cookie-free, privacy-first analytics
        service that does not collect personal data or track individual users.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare</strong>: serves and protects this website, and provides cookie-free
          analytics. Cloudflare processes traffic data under their GDPR-compliant Data Processing
          Agreement.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Google Analytics</strong> (consent required): provides usage analytics.
          Google processes data under their Data Processing Terms. IP anonymisation is enabled.
          Only loaded after you provide explicit consent.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain your personal data only for as long as is necessary for the purpose it was
        collected. Contact enquiries are retained for up to 12 months unless an ongoing business
        relationship exists.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under the UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Rectify</strong> any inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
        <li><strong>Erase</strong> your personal data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
        <li><strong>Restrict</strong> processing of your data</li>
        <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing of your data</li>
        <li><strong>Data portability</strong> to receive your data in a structured format</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:privacy@smagile.co">privacy@smagile.co</a>.
        We will respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you are not satisfied with how we have handled your data, you have the right to
        lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at
        <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</PublicLayout>
